# Diagram Images Git Ignore Example
# Rename this file to .gitignore to use it

# ============================================
# OPTION 1: Ignore all generated images
# ============================================
# Recommended if you regenerate images as needed
# Keeps repository lean (images are large binary files)

*.png
*.svg
*.pdf
*.jpg
*.jpeg

# Temporary mermaid files (should be auto-cleaned)
*.mmd

# ============================================
# OPTION 2: Include images in version control
# ============================================
# Use this if you want images committed to git
# Comment out the lines above and keep images

# (No exclusions - commit everything)

# ============================================
# OPTION 3: Selective image inclusion
# ============================================
# Keep some images, ignore others
# Example: Keep main diagrams, ignore detailed ones

# Ignore all by default
# *.png

# Then include specific ones
# !01-system-architecture-1.png
# !02-database-erd-1.png

# ============================================
# Always ignore temporary files
# ============================================

# Temporary mermaid files
*-temp-*.mmd

# Node modules (if running scripts locally)
node_modules/

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Editor files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
